# TaskFlow — Frontend

- Drag and drop: native HTML5 API only (no Sortable.js, etc.).
- `fetch` with `async`/`await`; use `AbortController` for timeouts/cancellation in `api.js`.
- Minimal shared state (e.g. board list in `app.js`); avoid heavy frameworks.
- Optimistic UI for task moves; on API failure, reload the board to resync.
- Kanban layout: CSS Grid with horizontal flow (`grid-auto-flow: column`, fixed/min column width ~280px).
- Priority visuals: left border color per priority; keep in sync with `escape.js` / API enums.
